US Bank Earnings Update

Key Earnings Insights

Growth And Profitability - Citigroup

Citigroup demonstrated strong growth and profitability in 2024, with net income up nearly 40% to $12.7 billion and a 5% revenue increase excluding divestitures. This performance was driven by growth across all five core businesses, positive operating leverage, and a smaller impact from Argentina's currency devaluation. The bank exceeded its full-year revenue target and improved its efficiency ratio.

  • ""For the full year, our net income was up nearly 40% to $12.7 billion.""
  • ""We exceeded our full year revenue target with revenues up 5% ex divestitures.""
  • ""Our 5 core businesses each generated positive operating leverage for the full year, which we also achieved at the firm level.""

Lending Activities - Citigroup

Lending activities contributed to revenue growth, particularly within USPB, which saw increased borrowing in card portfolios. The bank extended its co-branded partnership with American Airlines, aiming to enhance cardholder value and shareholder returns. While net interest income excluding Markets remained relatively flat overall, this was due to offsetting trends between USPB/Wealth growth and declines in Corporate/Other and Banking.

  • ""USPB revenues were up 6%, driven by borrowing across both card portfolios and by fee growth.""
  • ""We announced a 10-year extension of our co-branded partnership with American Airlines ensuring that this valuable relationship enters into its fifth decade.""
  • ""Net interest income, excluding Markets, was roughly flat, with growth in USPB and Wealth offset by declines in Corporate/Other and Banking.""

Growth And Profitability - Discover Financial Services

Discover Financial Services demonstrated strong growth and profitability in 2024, driven by loan growth, expanding deposits, higher net interest margin, and the sale of the student loan portfolio. Net income reached $4.5 billion for the full year, and earnings per share were $17.72. While card sales saw a modest slowdown, overall network volume increased due to the strength of the PULSE business.

  • ""We reported net income of $4.5 billion for the full year 2024, and earnings per share of $17.72, reflecting several factors.""
  • ""On a full year basis, we grew average loans, expanded our deposit base and benefited from a higher net interest margin.""
  • ""And despite a modest slowdown in U.S. card sales, overall network volume increased, driven by growth in our PULSE business and demonstrating the strength of our payments network.""

Lending Activities - Discover Financial Services

Discover saw modest growth in lending activities, with a focus on conservative underwriting in personal loans and credit tightening measures impacting card sales. The company plans to increase new account acquisition in the coming year, anticipating modest sales growth in 2025 and more substantial growth in 2026. Payment rates have stabilized and are expected to contribute less to loan growth going forward.

  • ""Card receivables increased 1% year-over-year due to a slightly lower payment rate, partially offset by a decrease in sales volume.""
  • ""Personal loans were up 5% from the prior year. Demand remains strong and we continue to take a conservative approach to underwriting.""
  • ""Holiday sales were strong and we currently see an opportunity to increase new account acquisition in the coming year. This is expected to provide a modest boost to 2025 sales with more substantial benefits expected in 2026.""

Growth And Profitability - Bread Financial

Bread Financial Holdings experienced mixed growth trends in Q4 2024. Credit sales saw a slight year-over-year increase driven by new partnerships and holiday spending, but overall revenue decreased due to lower finance charges, late fees, and merchant discount fees. Despite revenue declines, the company focused on operational efficiencies and expense discipline.

  • ""Credit sales of $7.9 billion increased 1% year-over-year, reflecting new partner growth and stronger holiday sales.""
  • ""Revenue was $0.9 billion for the quarter, down 9% year-over-year... due to lower finance charges and late fees, resulting from a gradual shift in risk and product mix, leading to a lower proportion of private label accounts.""
  • ""As a result of our expense discipline and efficiency gains, we delivered on our positive operating leverage goal, with lower expenses than our original 2024 full year guidance.""

Lending Activities - Bread Financial

Bread Financial Holdings focused on responsible growth within its lending activities, adapting to macroeconomic pressures and regulatory uncertainty. The company implemented credit tightening measures to maintain a stable credit risk distribution while also experiencing growth in co-brand and proprietary lending products during the holiday season. They continue to monitor economic uncertainties and anticipate continued growth in 2025.

  • ""Our strategic, proactive credit tightening actions during the year enabled us to maintain a stable credit risk distribution.""
  • ""Spending continues to be more heavily weighted towards nondiscretionary purchases, leading to strong loan growth in our co-brand and proprietary products during the holidays.""
  • ""While we continue to closely monitor ongoing economic and political uncertainties...we are cautiously optimistic that credit sales improvement will continue in 2025 driven by new and existing partner growth.""

Growth And Profitability - Synchrony Financial

Synchrony Financial experienced growth in new accounts, purchase volume, and loan receivables in Q4 2024, contributing to a strong overall performance for the year. Despite a dynamic environment, the company maintained profitability with disciplined cost management, achieving a solid return on assets and tangible common equity. Overall, 2024 was marked by significant growth in key metrics like purchase volume and new accounts.

  • ""We added 5 million new accounts, generated $48 billion of purchase volume and grew ending loan receivables by 2%.""
  • ""Our RSA continued to align the interest of both Synchrony and our partners, and we maintain our cost discipline to deliver fourth quarter net earnings of $774 million or $1.91 per diluted share, a return on average assets of 2.6% and a return on tangible common equity of 23%.""
  • ""This year marked our second highest level of purchase volume and serves as an important testament to the lasting appeal of our diverse and flexible financing solutions and compelling value propositions that we offer.""

Lending Activities - Synchrony Financial

Synchrony focused on diversifying its lending activities through new partnerships, expanding existing programs, and enhancing product utility. The company actively sought growth by offering flexible financing solutions across various industries and integrating new technologies like Synchrony Pay Later. Digital engagement played a key role, driving new account growth and lower acquisition costs.

  • ""During 2024, we added more than 45 new partners, including iconic brands like Virgin, Gibson and BRP as well as technology-oriented relationships like Adit Practice Management Software and ServiceTitan.""
  • ""Our long-term program extension and expansion will now include the introduction of Synchrony Pay Later, our buy now, pay later financing solution with 6-, 12- or 24-month installment payments.""
  • ""In addition, Synchrony enhanced the utility of a number of our private label credit cards by broadening their acceptance and expanding their distribution channels.""

Growth And Profitability - JPMorgan

JPMorgan Chase experienced strong growth and profitability in 2024, driven by record revenue and net income. While some areas like Banking & Wealth Management saw revenue declines due to deposit margin compression, other segments like Card Services, CIB, and AWM saw significant growth. The company expects continued, though moderated, growth in 2025.

  • ""2024 was another year of record revenue and net income, and we're proud of what we accomplished.""
  • ""In CIB, we had record revenue in Markets, Payments and Securities Services.""
  • ""In AWM, we had record long-term net inflows of $234 billion, positive across all channels, regions and asset classes.""

Lending Activities - JPMorgan

JPMorgan Chase saw mixed lending activity. While card outstandings grew significantly due to account acquisition and revolver growth, other areas like commercial and investment banking loans experienced declines due to paydowns and lower short-term financing. The company expects healthy card loan growth to continue in 2025, though at a slower pace.

  • ""Card outstandings were up 11% due to strong account acquisition and revolver growth.""
  • ""Global Corporate and Investment Banking loans were down 2% quarter-on-quarter, driven by paydowns and lower short-term financing, primarily offset by new originations.""
  • ""We expect healthy card loan growth again this year, but below the 12% pace we saw in 2024, as tailwinds from revolver normalization are largely behind us.""

Growth And Profitability - American Express

American Express experienced record revenues and net income in 2024, driven by strong card member spending, net card fees, and new card acquisitions. Their growth strategy, focused on value propositions, coverage expansion, and technology investments, has been successful, with momentum accelerating in Q4 2024. They project continued revenue and EPS growth in 2025.

  • ""2024 was another strong year for American Express. We delivered record revenues of $66 billion for the year, up 10% on an FX-adjusted basis, achieving our long-term aspiration.""
  • ""We had record net income of $10 billion with earnings per share of $14.01, up 25% for the year, which is higher than our long-term aspiration.""
  • ""We expect 2025 revenue growth of 8% to 10% and EPS of $15 to $15.50 or a 12% to 16% increase over 2024 adjusted for the Accertify gain.""

Lending Activities - American Express

Loan and receivable growth in Q4 2024 was 9%, moderating as expected compared to the pandemic recovery period. American Express anticipates loan and receivable growth to outpace spending growth in 2025 as they continue to cater to the evolving needs of their customer base.

  • ""Q4 Total loans and Card Member receivables grew at 9% on an FX-adjusted basis versus last year.""
  • ""As a reminder, these growth rates moderated over the course of the year as expected as we lap the period when customers were still building back revolving balances coming out of the pandemic.""
  • ""With that process largely behind us, for 2025, we expect loans and receivables growth to continue to grow a bit faster than spend...""

Growth And Profitability - Capital One

Capital One demonstrated steady top-line growth in Q4 2024, particularly in the Domestic Card business, coupled with strong margins. Profitability remained solid, though pre-provision earnings decreased slightly due to higher noninterest expenses, specifically in marketing and operating costs. Despite this, the full-year operating efficiency ratio remained in line with guidance.

  • ""In the fourth quarter, our Domestic Card business delivered another quarter of steady top line growth, strong margins and stable credit.""
  • ""Pre-provision earnings of $4.1 billion in the fourth quarter were down 13% from the third quarter driven by higher noninterest expense.""
  • ""Our full year operating efficiency ratio, net of adjustments, was 42.35%, consistent with our guidance of the low 42s""

Lending Activities - Capital One

Capital One saw continued growth in Domestic Card lending, with increased purchase volume and loan balances. In the auto sector, originations grew for the fourth consecutive quarter, leading to a return to loan balance growth. The company actively managed credit risk, tightening standards in previous periods and now capitalizing on market opportunities.

  • ""Year-over-year purchase volume growth for the quarter was 7%. Ending loan balances increased $8 billion or about 5% year-over-year.""
  • ""Auto originations were up 53% from the prior year quarter.""
  • ""With 4 consecutive quarters of originations growth in 2024, Consumer Banking loan balances returned to growth in the fourth quarter.""

Growth And Profitability - Wells Fargo

Wells Fargo demonstrated solid growth and profitability in Q4 2024, capping off a year of significant progress. Fee-based revenue growth offset declines in net interest income, aided by expense management and strategic investments. The bank also saw improved earnings per share and returned significant capital to shareholders.

  • ""Our solid performance this quarter caps a year of significant progress for Wells Fargo across multiple areas. Our earnings profile continues to improve.""
  • ""We grew net income and our diluted earnings per share was up 11% from a year ago.""
  • ""In 2024, our strong fee-based revenue growth, up 15% from a year ago, largely offset the expected decline in net interest income, reflecting these efforts.""

Lending Activities - Wells Fargo

Average loans declined over the year due to weak loan demand and credit tightening, despite growth in credit card balances. This decline was offset by growth in deposit-gathering businesses, allowing the bank to reduce reliance on high-cost corporate treasury CDs. The bank also secured a significant partnership with Volkswagen and Audi as their preferred purchase finance provider.

  • ""Average loans declined throughout the year as...growth in credit card balances was offset by declines in most other asset classes, reflecting weak loan demand as well as credit tightening actions.""
  • ""Average deposits grew from fourth quarter 2023, with growth in our deposit gathering-businesses, enabling us to reduce higher-cost CDs issued by corporate treasury.""
  • ""In our auto business, we announced a multiyear co-branded agreement where we will be the preferred purchase finance provider for Volkswagen and Audi brands in the United States starting in the first half of this year.""
